</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="AP12_confines">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">AP12 confines</rdfs:label>
    <skos:notation>AP12</skos:notation>
    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">confines</skos:prefLabel>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="A3_Stratigraphic_Interface"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="A2_Stratigraphic_Volume_Unit"/>
    <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="AP12i_is_confined_by"/>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Quantification: many to many (0,n:0,n)

Scope note:
This property identifies partly or completely the surface (A3 Stratigraphic Interface) of an A2 Stratigraphic Volume Unit. One A3 Stratigraphic Interface may confine two or more A2 Stratigraphic Volume Units.

Examples:
- The Stratigraphic Interface “[19]” (A3) confines the Stratigraphic Volume Unit “(2)” (A2) –see Figure 4a, above.

In First Order Logic:
- AP12(x,y) ⇒ A3(x)
- AP12(x,y) ⇒ A2(y)
</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
